Replace this file's contents with the Argon2id hash of your admin token,
on a single line, no trailing newline. Then save the file as
`admin_token` (no extension) in the same directory.

How to generate one:

  docker run --rm -it vaultwarden/server:1.35.7 /vaultwarden hash

The command will prompt for the cleartext token, hash it with sane Argon2id
parameters, and print a string that begins with `$argon2id$v=19$m=...`.

Vaultwarden reads the file via the `_FILE` indirection configured in
compose.yaml (`ADMIN_TOKEN_FILE=/run/secrets/vaultwarden_admin_token`).

Operational notes:
  - Treat the cleartext token like any password manager root password.
    Anyone who knows it has full admin control of the vault.
  - Rotating the token only requires rewriting this file and recreating
    the container (`scripts/homelab.sh restart vaultwarden`).
  - The actual file `admin_token` is git-ignored. Only this `.example`
    file is committed.
